TITLE: Student Barista/Espresso (Ongoing Pool of Applicants 2018-2019) WORK STUDY ONLY
DESCRIPTION:
Job Summary

(Purpose)

  • Assist in the daily operations of running an espresso bar with consistent espresso drinks and exceptional customer service.
  • Must be dependable, attentive to detail, ability to follow through with oral and written instructions from managers and supervisors.

(Educational Benefits)
• Will provide customer service experience.
• Will enforce academic disciplines such as algebra, geometry, trigonometry, and calculus by providing opportunity to practice arithmetic while making change.
• Will enhance a basic understanding of chemistry, especially as involved in preparing coffee beverages.
• Handling money provides a firm foundation for accounting and economic studies.



Minimum Qualifications

(Skills)

  • Professionalism is expected when dealing with customers.
  • Must be dependable, attentive to detail, ability to follow through with oral and written instructions from managers and supervisors.
  • Perform basic math, organizing, and problem-solving.
  • Work assigned schedule.
  • Be able to pass a background check.
  • Able to work weekday evenings and weekends.
  • Have a Food Handler’s Permit.
  • It is essential to be able to meet the physical demands of standing for prolonged periods of time, using repetitive arm, hand, and finger movements. A percentage of the shift will require some amount of stooping, kneeling, crouching, lifting, walking, carrying or moving and other movements. On occasion it will be necessary to lift up to 35 lbs, sometimes repetitively, and reach shelves overhead and below knees. This position requires sharing a work area and will require a flexible schedule, including occasional weekend and evening work.
  • Must be eligible for student employment in the quarter in which you are working.

Preferred Qualifications

  • Barista experience.
  • Cash handling experience.
  • Qualified for work study through the Financial Aid Office.

 

 



How To Apply

To apply for this position, you must complete the on-line application and attach:

  • Resume which includes three references (references are optional)
  • Schedule of availability

The schedule is available at http://www.lib.cwu.edu/sites/default/files/StudentScheduleForJobPools.doc

For questions, please contact:
Name: Alison Mattson
Email: Alison.Mattson@cwu.edu
Website: Brooks Library

Please contact Human Resources at hr@cwu.edu or 509-963-1202 if you require technical assistance with the on-line application process.

TITLE: CWU Business Ambassador
DESCRIPTION:
Job Summary

(Purpose)

  • As a Student ambassador you will be enforcing recruitment efforts for the College of Business, assist in event planning, collaborate with professional individuals and help manage the College of Business brand.
  • The ambassador will assist in providing information about events attended, for an up to date webpage and social media.
  • They will also assist in daily office tasks such as answering emails, phone calls, and promoting events.
  • On occasion they will be asked to speak publicly to a small or large audience at events or for recruitment.
  • Students are expected to start work within the quarter they apply.
  • Ideal candidates for this position would be students who are admitted into their major, self-starters, experienced speakers, team players, and are very organized.

 
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION FOR APPLICANTS
(Educational Benefits)

The College of Business is all about launching their students to a better future through engagement and strong partnerships. Within joining the Student Ambassador team, you will be able to do so with these provided opportunities:

  • Opportunity to network with university staff and faculty along with industry professionals
  • Ability to add valuable work and leadership experience into your portfolio
  • Become more knowledgeable about the College of Business programs & opportunities
  • Apply leadership developmental training into a professional setting
  • Become familiar with the day-to-day inner working of a university office environment


Minimum Qualifications

Preferred Qualifications

  • Held leadership position in CB or CWU club 
  • Current College of Business major
  • Bilingual public speaker
  • Familiar with Photoshop and Microsoft 360 (Office, Excel, Outlook, PowerPoint).
  • Experience in event planning/set up

 

Desired Knowledge, Skills and Abilities

  • Knowledge of College of Business clubs, majors, and programs.
  • Familiar with Social media platforms (Twitter, Instagram, Facebook, Linkedin)
  • Knows other leaders on or off campus, Sociable/friendly attitude
  • Public speaking skills (small to large crowds)
  • Ability to think creatively, work well under pressure, & collaborate on a team effectively.
  • Can adequately communicate through proper phone etiquette and email.
  • Listen and assess needs effectively
  • Completed a minimum of 2 terms at CWU
  • Collegiate GPA of 3.0 or higher
  • Must be eligible for student employment in the quarter in which you apply to work
  • Must have a current driver’s license and willing to travel within the state


How To Apply

To apply for this position, you must complete the on-line application and attach:

  • Cover letter;
  • Resume;
  • Class Schedule; and
  • References

For questions, please contact:

TITLE: Student Learning Commons Tutoring (Ongoing Pool for 2018/2019 Academic Year)
DESCRIPTION:
Job Summary

(Purpose):

A tutor fosters independent learning and student’s understanding of course material, stimulates active learning, and facilitates student insights into the learning process by providing peer-to-peer collaborative learning in individual or small groups. Tutors maintain an effective learning environment by providing support to students in meeting course outcomes and helping students develop effective study skills.



Minimum Qualifications

(Skills Needed):

  • Minimum of 45 credits with a cumulative GPA of at least 3.25, or a cumulative GPA of at least 3.25 for your last 45 credits and a faculty recommendation
  • Previous grade of at least B+ in the course to be tutored or a higher-level course that covers the same material in more depth, or a cumulative GPA of at least 3.25 in a content area and a faculty recommendation
  • Ability to enroll in the one-credit tutor training course (UNIV 201: Tutoring Strategies), leading to a tutor certification through the College Reading and Learning Association (CRLA) either the quarter of hire or the following quarter
  • Excellent interpersonal, communication, and study skills
  • Ability to work well with a diverse student population
  • Ability to function effectively as a member of a team that values transparency, honesty, service, collaboration, and communication
  • Ability to work independently
  • Must be eligible for student employment in the quarter in which you are working

Educational Benefits

  • Learn how to assess students’ needs
  • Learn to work with others in collaboration
  • Opportunity to attend conferences
  • Gain teaching experience in their academic field
  • Master a subject more effectively by teaching it to others
  • Enhance interpersonal, communication, and leadership skills
  • Earn certification through the College Reading and Learning Association


How To Apply

To apply for this position, you must complete the on-line application and attach:

  • Cover letter
  • Resume
  • References (CWU Faculty references strongly preferred)

For questions, please contact:

Name: Katie Boswell
Email: katie.boswell@cwu.edu

* Please contact Human Resources at hr@cwu.edu or 509-963-1202 if you require technical assistance with the on-line application process.

TITLE: Student International Peer Advisor (IPA) (Ongoing Pool of Applicants 2018-2019)
DESCRIPTION:
Job Summary

(Purpose)

  • The IPA position is an integral part of the Asia University America Program (AUAP). The program exists at CWU, WWU, and EWU, and is a contracted study abroad program with Asia University in Tokyo, Japan.
  • IPAs heavily influence whether a student has a positive or negative experience!
  • As a member of a team of 4- 8 other IPAs, you would be a resource person for a group of 8-13 students from Japan.

(Educational Benefits)

  • IPAs can improve their leadership, communication skills, and people skills, their cross-cultural knowledge, knowledge of CWU and Ellensburg, and decision-making ability.
  • This is a chance to make new friends, have a profoundly positive impact on other peoples’ lives, and enrich your college life, while gaining necessary job skills applicable to an immense variety of employment fields.


Minimum Qualifications

(Skills)

  • Full-time student status.
  • Must reside in one of the designated residence halls (usually the Bassetties or Carmody/Al-Monty) with the students.
  • Flexible/responsible
  • Good organization skills
  • Open to learning new things
  • Genuine interest in the welfare of the students from Japan
  • Must be eligible for student employment in the quarter(s) in which you are working

Preferred Qualifications

  • Valid driver’s license is preferred.


How To Apply

We accept applications throughout the year, as we hire new IPAs in May for Fall/Winter cycles and in January for Spring/Summer.  We also sometimes hire assistant IPAs to train for the following cycle and to fill in for IPAs should one of them have to leave their position suddenly.

Anticipated start date for Fall/Winter 2018 is Saturday, September 1st, 2018.  However, applicants must also be available for extended interview/training sessions which will meet from May until the end of the quarter depending on the applicants’ schedules.  AUAP students will arrive at CWU on Friday, September 7th, and leave the US on Saturday, February 2nd, 2019. Online applications will be due by Sunday, May 6th, 2018.


To apply for this position, you must complete the on-line application and attach:
• Cover letter
• Resume (Including personal and/or work references 
• Class/work schedules—current quarter and finals


For questions, contact the supervisor,

Email: Werdinm@cwu.edu

Location: International Center, Room 137

TITLE: Student Communications Specialist/Dispatcher (Ongoing pool 2018/2019)
DESCRIPTION:
Job Summary

Job Summary (Purpose):

This position is responsible for operating several support functions associated with flight activities including dispatching, data collection, flight following, and other customer service items as required by the CWU Department of Aviation. Position will coordinate dispatching activities with student employees, flight instructors, and line and maintenance personnel. Facilitate all of the aircraft transfers from one student/instructor to the next. Provides a professional environment for the CWU students/instructors and verifies all flight-related reports and documents to ensure safety.

Job Duties (Essential Functions):

  • Provide a high level of customer satisfaction and maintain a department image appropriate to CWU as a leader in Aviation Education
  • Provide accurate data for aircraft/Flight Training Dispatcher check in and room assignments to insure proper billing for all flight and FTD transactions daily.
  • Track student lab progress reports using Talon Systems ETA cloud based software and issue reports for lab grading purposes
  • Coordinate and debrief pilots on aircraft discrepancies, assure proper documentation, and report to maintenance technicians in an expedient manner

Flight Training Dispatching Requirements:
1. Adheres to the applicable guidelines of CWU Flight Training when performing all duties.
2. Identifies ways to integrate process improvements and efficiencies for various job functions.
3. Dispatch and coordinate with various departments on a routine basis to cover aircraft (i.e. aircraft maintenance, fueling and cleaning).
4. Assists in maintaining safety in flight operations.
5. Maintains aircraft supplies and subscriptions.
6. Assist with the evaluation of the weather for departure/arrival flights to determine trip feasibility.
7. Provides the highest level of service and safety for all students and instructors.
8. Maintains current and accurate information on the Flight Status & Information board.
9. Provides coordination of aircraft malfunctions and/or inspections between flight crew and maintenance.
10. Completes fleet efficiency tracking forms and reports on time.
11. Monitors telephone system and provides prompt response to issues.
Other duties as assigned

Required Qualifications (Skills Needed):

  • Demonstrated working knowledge of Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) regulations related to flight school operations
  • Knowledge of all aspects flight operations
  • Knowledge of air traffic control terminology and procedures
  • Knowledge of proper radio voice procedures
  • Experience and/or training that demonstrates the ability to use Word, Excel, e-mail, database management and internet and/or similar software applications
  • Excellent customer service experience
  • Excellent interpersonal and organizational skills
  • Attention to detail and strong time management skills
  • Ability to implement and follow a general emergency plan
  • Ability to read, understand and explain current weather reports, forecasts, and aircraft performance charts
  • Ability to express oneself clearly and concisely in written and spoken English
  • Ability to understand verbal and written instructions to facilitate the decision-making process and safety
  • Ability to communicate effectively with Flight Training students, management and staff
  • Ability to plan and prioritize work efficiently

Preferred Skills:

  • Dispatching experience with 14CFR 141 flight school operations
  • Dispatching experience with 14CFR 121, 135 or Military flight operations
  • Experience using Talon ETA cloud based flight school tracking software
  • Collegiate flight school program operations experience

Educational Benefits:
This experience can be translated into many administrative and/or industry applicable experience for future careers.



How To Apply

To apply for this position, you must complete the on-line application and attach:

  • Cover letter
  • Resume
  • Schedule of Availability
  • Class Schedule

TITLE: Student Ambassador - Lynwood Campus
DESCRIPTION:
Job Summary

Purpose:

  • Be responsible for fostering awareness of CWU Lynnwood academic programs
  • Attract prospective new students to CWU-Lynnwood
  • Promote dual enrollment (an early admission to the University for Washington State Community College students).
  • With direction and oversight from the Regional Director and Secretary Senior, plan, coordinates, and direct activities that strengthen relationships and identify prospective students on campus who may be interested in transferring to CWU-Lynnwood


Minimum Qualifications

(Skills Needed):

  • Must be a current CWU student in good standing
  • Must have strong communication abilities (written and interpersonal), outgoing personality, and good organization skills
  • Must be reliable, dependable, punctual, trustworthy, ethical, courteous, respectful, self-motivated, and able to work independently
  • Ability to actively engage students, employees, and community members is required
  • Excellent leadership, initiative and customer services skills are essential
  • Must have a flexible work schedule

Preferred Qualifications

  • Past experience in leadership positions
  • Bilingual

Educational Benefits

  • Marketing, promoting, and networking
  • Public speaking
  • Problem solving
  • Managing and visionary planning
  • Collaboration and team building skills
  • Student leadership skills
  • Mentoring from Regional Director and Secretary Senior
  • Ability to add outreach and leadership skills to your portfolio
  • Become more knowledgeable about CWU-Lynnwood programs, services and opportunities
  • Experience Higher Education working environment


How To Apply

To apply for this position, you must complete the on-line application and attach:

  • Cover letter;
  • Resume;
  • Schedule of Availability
  • Class Schedule; and
  • References
